My favourite rainbows are the ones that appear after a summer storm. They look like giant, curved bridges made of bright, shiny colours. Red is at the top, followed by orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, and violet at the bottom.

I love them because they seem to dance across the sky. Sometimes they are so high up that you can only see the very top arch. Other times, they stretch low over the green grass, making the flowers look like they are wearing rainbow hats.

When I see one, I feel happy and wonder how it is possible for the sun and the rain to make such a beautiful picture. It feels like magic. I imagine little fairies painting the sky with their brushes. Even though they are only there for a few minutes, they make the whole world feel special. I always wait for the clouds to part so I can see the next one. [end of text]


